# aircraft-health-cag-demo
# Portfolio project demonstrating Context Augmented Generation using a Knowledge Graph

## Purpose
Demonstrate Cognite Data Fusion (CDF) architecture at small scale:
IT/OT/ET ingestion → Industrial Knowledge Graph → CAG agent

## Stack
- Frontend: TypeScript / React (Vite, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui)
- Backend: Python (FastAPI, uvicorn)
- CDF queries: cognite-sdk Python client → mock server
- LLM: Anthropic SDK (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)

## Architecture — NEVER DEVIATE
- Mock CDF server: FastAPI implementing real CDF REST API patterns
- Standard CDF resources (Assets, TimeSeries, Datapoints, Events,
  Relationships, Files): always via cognite-sdk Python client
- Extended fleet resources (policies, fleet_owners): httpx to mock CDF base URL —
  same auth, same {"items": [...]} envelope, never direct JSON file reads
- Context assembly: graph traversal only — no vector store, no embeddings (to showcase unique CAG benefits)
- Agent: ReAct loop with function calling, streaming via SSE
- All CDF routes POST, response envelope always { "items": [...] }

## Fleet
Four 1978 Cessna 172N aircraft, Desert Sky Aviation, KPHX
- N4798E
- N2251K
- N8834Q
- N1156P

All fleet information is stored in a single Knowledge Graph.

## Relationship types
- HAS_COMPONENT: Aircraft → Component
- IS_TYPE: Engine component → ENGINE_MODEL node
  (allows agent to compare sensor trends across all aircraft with the same engine)
- PERFORMED_ON: MaintenanceEvent → Component
- GOVERNED_BY: Aircraft → FleetOwner (bidirectional traversable)
- HAS_POLICY: FleetOwner → OperationalPolicy
- REFERENCES_AD: MaintenanceEvent → AD document
- IDENTIFIED_ON: SquawkEvent → Component
- LINKED_TO: Document → Aircraft or Component
No PRECEDED, FOUND_CONDITION, CAUSED_BY, EXHIBITED, or OBSERVED_ON edges — causal
patterns discovered via chronological event traversal and IS_TYPE time-series
cross-fleet comparison, not hardcoded cause-effect edges.

## Cross-aircraft pattern discovery
The agent finds connections between N8834Q sensor anomalies and N1156P
history by:
1. get_time_series_trend(aircraft_id, metric): retrieve last-N datapoints,
   compute trend direction and caution threshold check
2. compare_engine_sensor_across_fleet(aircraft_id, metric): traverse IS_TYPE →
   ENGINE_MODEL → all peer engines → retrieve sensor windows, including
   pre-failure windows for aircraft with a grounding squawk
3. get_engine_type_history(aircraft_id): traverse IS_TYPE →
   ENGINE_MODEL → all engines of same type → chronological event history
4. search_fleet_for_similar_events(description): keyword match
   across pilot_notes, squawk descriptions
Never via hardcoded causal edges.

## N1156P causal story
Told through chronological timestamped events only:
- Flight events with deteriorating pilot_notes over 6 months
- Escalating squawk events
- EngineFailure event at failure date
- Post-accident inspection event with findings in description
No graph edges assert causation — timeline is the causal chain.

## Code standards
- Python: PEP 8, type hints, explicit error handling
- TypeScript: strict mode, explicit error handling
- No placeholders or TODOs — implement fully
- Log every traversed node: [CAG] Traversed: {node_type}:{external_id}
- Python functions: docstring explaining CDF concept mirrored

## Ports
- Mock CDF: 4000
- API: 3000
- Vite: 5173

## CogniteClient (Python)
config = ClientConfig(
    client_name="aircraft-health-cag-demo",
    project="desert_sky",
    base_url="http://localhost:4000",
    credentials=Token("mock-token")
)
client = CogniteClient(config)

## File ownership
- mock_cdf/: mock server — do not modify architecture
- src/agent/: CAG context assembly and agent — core
- src/ingest/: CSV → mock CDF pipeline
- scripts/: dataset.py + transform scripts only
- client/: React frontend only
- data/: generated files — do not manually edit